<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Britain-Drugs     09-15 0147</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Britain-Drugs,0153</SECOND>
<HEAD>Record Drug Seizures Last Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Britain last year made a record 38,000 drug
seizures and convicted a record 30,500 offenders, Home Secretary
Douglas Hurd said.
   The $13 million worth of drugs seized last year is nearly seven
times the $2 million total in 1987.
   Hurd said 94 percent of the increase was attributed to marijuana
seizures.
   The 700 pounds of cocaine seized last year is three times higher
than the 1986 level, although lower than the nearly 900 pounds
seized in 1987.
   ``This ... confirms the need for our action to choke off the
supply of this drug while maintaining our efforts to reduce demand
for it, particularly in the form of crack,'' Hurd said.
   The number of drug seizures in 1988 was 25 percent higher than in
1987, and the number of convictions for drug offenses was 16 percent
higher.
</TEXT>
