<DOCNO> AP890915-0054 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-09-15-89 0628EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     09-15 0508</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0519</SECOND>
<HEAD>Showers, Dense Fog in Northeast</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Heavy rain that fell over parts of the Northeast was accompanied
early today by dense fog, while scattered showers and thunderstorms
dampened an area from the central Gulf coast to the mid-Atlantic
states.
   Fog also blanketed sections of Ohio, Indiana and Kentucky. Cloudy
skies lingered from the lower Ohio Valley and the middle Mississippi
Valley to the western Gulf coast, but clear skies prevailed across
much of the rest of the nation.
   The upper Great Lakes region, upper Mississippi Valley and
northern Rockies were chilly early today, with temperatures in the
30s and 40s.
   Hurricane Hugo today moved slowly toward the Caribbean, packing
115 mph winds late Thursday, and hurricane forecasters warned
islanders to prepare for heavy winds and rain, which should begin
within the next 48 hours.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms extending
from the East Coast across the Ohio and Tennessee valleys to the
middle Mississippi Valley, with the most rainfall from New England
across the Appalachians to the Ohio Valley; and widely scattered
thunderstorms over California.
   Predicted highs: in the 60s from northern New England across the
Great Lakes region to Missouri, and over portions of the Pacific
Coast; into the 90s over Florida and interior valleys of California;
between 100 and 105 degrees in the desert Southwest; and in the 70s
and 80s over much of the rest of the country.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 36
degrees at Yellowstone Park, Wyo., to 84 degrees at Phoenix and
Yuma, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Albany, N.Y., 58 drizzle; Atlanta 76 partly cloudy; Boston
65 drizzle; Buffalo 53 drizzle; Charleston, S.C., 77 thunderstorm;
Chattanooga 71 foggy; Cincinnati 62 foggy; Cleveland 61 foggy;
Detroit 49 fair; Hatteras 75 partly cloudy; Jacksonville 73 foggy;
Key West 84 cloudy; Knoxville 70 foggy; Macon 74 fair; Miami 79
cloudy; New York 74 cloudy; Philadelphia 74 foggy; Pittsburgh 61
cloudy; Portland, Maine, 55 rain; Richmond 73 cloudy; Tampa 75 fair;
Washington, D.C., 75 partly cloudy.
   _Central: Birmingham 71 showery; Bismarck 54 fair; Chicago 59
fair; Denver 51 fair; Des Moines 49 fair; Fort Worth 56 fair;
Indianapolis 56 foggy; Kansas City 48 fair; Little Rock 62 foggy;
Louisville 62 drizzle; Memphis 64 cloudy; Nashville 64 foggy; New
Orleans 76 cloudy; North Platte 47 fair; Oklahoma City 52 fair;
Omaha 48 fair; Rapid City 53 fair; St. Louis 59 cloudy;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 50 fair; Sault Ste. Marie 40 fair; San Antonio
66 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 57 fair; Anchorage 48 partly cloudy; Boise 63
fair; Casper 55 fair; Fairbanks 42 fair; Great Falls 52 fair;
Honolulu 78 fair; Las Vegas 70 fair; Los Angeles 68 fair; Medford 66
fair; Pendleton 67 fair; Portland, Ore., 61 fair; Reno 59 fair; Salt
Lake City 54 fair; San Diego 71 cloudy; San Francisco 55 fair;
Seattle 59 fair; Spokane 57 fair.
   _International: Calgary 54 partly cloudy; Montreal 55 rain;
Ottawa 54 cloudy; Regina 52 fair; Toronto 54 partly cloudy; Winnipeg
57 fair; San Juan 77 fair.
