<FIRST>r a PM-ChildRapist     09-15 0332</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Child Rapist,0341</SECOND>
<HEAD>10-Year-Old Accused Of Serial Sexual Assaults</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA CLARA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 10-year-old boy was arrested and
accused of a series of sexual assualts on his playmates who range in
age from 4 to 10, police said.
   The youth was taken into custody Aug. 21 after an interview with
Sgt. Phil Zaragossa, who said the boy first denied allegations of
attacks on two boys and two girls at his Santa Clara apartment
complex, authorities said.
   ``Then, he makes a few slips and leads me to believe he does know
what's going on,'' the officer said. ``Finally, he admitted to
sodomy. He starts to cry and asks if he's going to jail.''
   The child was emotionless while describing the assaults that
allegedly occurred in parking stalls and in a laundry room starting
in May, and said he learned about sodomy from pornographic
magazines, police said.
   The boy was taken to Santa Clara Juvenile Center after his
arrest, and later released to a female friend of his mother's on the
condition that he see a counselor daily and not associate with his
alleged victims, police said.
   If the youngster is convicted of sexually attacking his friends,
he could spend up to eight years in court custody for each criminal
count. He could be placed in a group home or treatment facility, or
released to his mother with a requirement that he receive more
counseling.
   No court date was set.
   ``I don't know if it's that kids don't know that it's wrong or
that it's the type of environment they're in,'' said Deputy District
Attorney Cynthia Sevely, who will prosecute the case.
   Zaragossa said he wasn't particularly shocked by the allegations.
   ``There are a lot more incidents like these being committed,'' he
said. ``Everybody wants to close their eyes and turn their head if
they hear about it.''
   Of the 27 juveniles with hearings pending in Santa Clara County
for sex-related crimes, this youth is by far the youngest, officials
said.
</TEXT>
