<HEAD>Capital Punishment For Opium, Cannabis and Cocaine Trafficking</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SINGAPORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government Friday announced plans to amend
drug laws to mandate the death penalty for trafficking of opium,
marijuana and cocaine.
   `` We have invested a tremendous amount of manpower, public money
and energy in keeping out streets free of drugs. However, because of
the worsening global situation on drugs, we have to be even more
vigilant,'' Home Affairs Minister Shanmugam Jayakumar said in
announcing the planned crackdown.
</TEXT>
