<HEAD>Taxi Hijacker Surrenders Hostages</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COPENHAGEN, Denmark (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman demanding morphine hijacked a
taxi Friday and took two hostages on an eight-hour ride through
Copenhagen before he was arrested, police and news reports said. No
one was injured.
   The 34-year-old hijacker, wielding a sawed-off shotgun,
commandeered the cab, took the driver hostage and later forced a
27-year-old woman into the taxi, news reports said.
   The man contacted police on radio, demanding morphine and a
syringe, and said he planned to kill himself with an overdose.
Newspaper reports said he was distraught over family problems.
   Police followed the taxi at a discreet distance as it drove
through the city streets for eight hours.
   The ordeal ended when police promised to let the man go free and
he released the hostages. He was later arrested in a Copenhagen
apartment, they said.
