   American soprano Michele Crider, Italian tenor
Roberto Sacca, and West German bass Reinhard Hagen are the top
winners of Geneva's annual International Competition for Musical
Performers, it was announced Friday.
   The singers each won $5,880 and qualified for another contest
scheduled next March that will be broadcast throughout Europe.
   Ms. Crider, a 30-year-old Quincy, Ill. native, was also a
