<FIRST>r i AM-Netherlands-Cocaine     09-15 0182</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Netherlands-Cocaine,0187</SECOND>
<HEAD>Cocaine Worth $32 Million Seized in Netherlands</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Colombia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TILBURG, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About $32 milllion of cocaine hidden
in containers of asphalt was seized and eight people arrested when
Dutch authorities intercepted a drug shipment from South America,
law enforcement officials said Friday.
   Among those arrested were three Colombians and a Belgian, but
Dutch officials declined to further identify the suspects.
   The arrests Thursday night capped six months of detective work,
and coincided with the delivery of the drugs, which were concealed
in 21 barrels of asphalt at an abandoned dairy plant near this
southern city, according to police spokesman Carel Bouwman.
   It was not immediately where the cocaine originated, but Bouwman
said it crossed the Atlantic aboard a Venezuelan container ship that
arrived earlier this month in Antwerp, a Belgian port 30 miles from
Tilburg.
   The drug bust was one of the biggest in the Netherlands this year.
   In April, 310 pounds of cocaine was seized at Amsterdam's
Schiphol Airport, while earlier this year West German authorities
confiscated 1,430 pounds of the drug in Munich, Bouwman said.
</TEXT>
