<FIRST>r w AM-Bush-Haiti     09-15 0090</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bush-Haiti,90</SECOND>
<HEAD>Adams Appointed Ambassador to Haiti</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush on Friday announced he would
nominate Alvin P. Adams, a terrorism specialist at the State
Department, to be U.S. ambassador to Haiti.
   Adams, of Alexandria, Va., would succeed Brunson McKinley.
   Since 1987, Adams, 48, has served as the associate coordinator
for counter terrorism at the State Department.
   He is also a former ambassador to Djibouti, was a staff member of
the National Security council in the Nixon administration and was
U.S. political officer in Saigon in 1971-74.
</TEXT>
