<FIRST>s i BC-RushdieDates Adv24   09-15 0320</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Rushdie Dates, Adv 24,0332</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv24</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Sunday, Sept. 24, and thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>Key Dates in Salman Rushdie's Year of Furor</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-Rushdie's Year, b0633-b0634</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are the dates of key events in the furor over
``The Satanic Verses'':
   SEPT. 26, 1988 _ Viking Penguin publishes ``The Satanic Verses''
in London.
   OCT. 5 _ India bans the book as offensive to Islam, the first
country to do so.
   JAN. 14, 1989 _ Moslems publicly burn the book in Bradford,
northern England.
   FEB. 12-13 _ Seven people are killed in anti-Rushdie rioting in
Pakistan and India.
   FEB. 14 _ Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini of Iran calls on Moslems to
kill Rushdie and his publishers on grounds they insulted Islam.
Rushdie and his wife, Marianne Wiggins, go into hiding.
   FEB. 15 _ Protesters stone the British Embassy in Tehran, Iran's
capital. An Iranian cleric puts a price on Rushdie's head.
   FEB. 17 _ President Ali Khamenei of Iran suggests Rushdie could
be pardoned if he repents.
   FEB. 18 _ Rushdie apologizes for causing distress to Moslems.
Khomeini renews the death sentence, saying the statement falls short
of a public repentance.
   FEB. 21 _ The 12-nation European Economic Community withdraws its
envoys from Iran. All but Britain's return within weeks.
   MARCH 7 _ Britain and Iran sever diplomatic relations.
   MARCH 29 _ The Saudi Arabian leader of Moslems in Belgium who
criticized Khomeini's death sentence is shot dead at Brussels' main
mosque along with an aide.
   AUG. 3 _ A man is killed in a bomb explosion at a London hotel,
while purportedly preparing an attack on Rushdie.
   AUG. 25 _ Ms. Wiggins' publishers say she has been living apart
from her husband for the last month.
   SEPT. 1 _ In his first published literary work since ``The
Satanic Verses,'' a 17-line poem in Granta, a British literary
magazine, Rushdie vows to continue writing.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Sunday Sept. 24</NOTE>
</DOC>
