<TEXT>
   Junk bond trading slowed as the cash crunch at
Campeau Corp. weighed heavily on the market, with traders
considering whether the company's problems were a forerunner of
trouble in a wide variety of the high-risk securities.
   Trading slowed Thursday one day after admissions that Campeau's
Allied Stores Corp. and Federated Department Stores Inc. units could
default on their debt payments triggered a broad junk bond selloff.
</TEXT>
