head the Securities and Exchange Commission, told a Senate committee
he believed one can be a free marketeer and still be a tough cop on
Wall Street.
   Illegal activities such as price fixing or insider trading are
``an attack on the market itself,'' Breeden told the Senate Banking,
Housing and Urban Affairs Committee at his confirmation hearing
Thursday.
</TEXT>
