<FIRST>r f PM-WPPSSBonds     09-15 0237</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-WPPSS Bonds,0248</SECOND>
<HEAD>WPPSS Executive Board Approves $721.4 Million Bond Sale</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Washington Public Power Supply System's
executive board has approved the sale of $721.4 million in refunding
bonds for two mothballed nuclear power plants.
   The supply system had planned to offer $450 million worth of
high-interest bonds for resale, but demand resulted in the higher
offering.
   The bonds will be sold over the next several weeks. The executive
board acted Thursday.
   Investors will be offered tax-exempt bonds with annual yields
ranging from 6.25 percent to 7.7 percent, with the long-range bonds
maturing as far in the future as the year 2015.
   The bonds are secured by agreements that obligate payment by the
Bonneville Power Administration.
   Proceeds from the sale will be used to refund bonds sold in 1981
and 1982 and carrying interest rates as high as 15 percent.
   The supply system plans to refinance a total of about $2 billion
in bonds sold to pay for construction on plants Nos. 1 and 3, both
of which have been mothballed unfinished.
   WPPSS also wants to refinance about $800 million in high-interest
bonds for plant No. 2, which is operating.
   The supply system estimates annual savings from the entire
refunding package will be $70 million to $80 million annually.
   The No. 1 and No. 2 plants are at the Hanford nuclear reservation
in Eastern Washington; No. 3 is at Satsop, west of Olympia.
</TEXT>
