<FILEID>AP-NR-09-15-89 1430EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f AM-SteelImports     09-15 0167</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Steel Imports,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Imports Down in July</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel imports fell 5.9 percent to 1.46 million
tons in July compared with the previous month and represented 19.3
percent of the domestic supply, the American Iron and Steel
Institute reported Friday.
   Steel imports for the first seven months of 1989 were 10.2
million tons, down 19.7 percent from the same period last year and
representing 17.5 percent of domestic supply, the trade group
reported.
   Steel exports in July amounted to 303,000 tons, down 24.8 percent
from June, the group said. In July 1988, American steel
manufacturers exported 128,000 tons.
   The American Institute for Imported Steel Inc., which represents
leading steel importers and exporters, said imports for the first
seven months amounted to 15.2 percent of domestic demand when
semifinished steel bound for U.S. mills is excluded.
   The steel import group noted the percentage without semifinished
steel is below the Bush administration's Voluntary Restraint
Agreements target of 18.5 percent of imported steel in the domestic
market.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
