   The stock market turned in a mixed showing Friday, showing few
ill effects from the quarterly ``triple witching hour.'' The Dow
Jones industrial average rose 9.69 to 2,674.58, reducing its loss
for the week to 34.96 points.
   The dollar fell sharply in panicky domestic dealings.
   Bond prices finished higher.
   Gold futures prices made strong gains; energy futures advanced;
grains and soybeans were mixed; and livestock and meat futures were
mixed.
