<DOCNO> AP890915-0288 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-09-15-89 2157EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f AM-Amoco-UnitedKingdom     09-15 0182</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Amoco-United Kingdom,0189</SECOND>
<HEAD>Amoco Hires Morgan Stanley to Investigate Sale of UK Operations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Amoco's United Kingdom operations announced Friday
that Morgan Stanley International had been hired to look into the
possible sale of its refining and petroleum marketing operations
there.
   Chicago-based Amoco Corp. said it has been approached by parties
interested in acquiring the facilities, which include a 70 percent
interest in the Milford Haven, Wales, refinery and a 10 percent
interest in the Mainline Pipeline, about 250 service stations and
its interest in five product terminals.
   The sale would not include Amoco's synthetic fabric operations in
Dundee and Consett, or other affiliates in the United Kingdom, the
company said.
   Amoco said it is considering selling the refining and petroleum
product marketing operations as part of a long-term strategy to
divest such operations outside the United States.
   Amoco subsidiaries sold refining and marketing operations in
Italy, Australia and India in the mid-1980s.
   The Milford Haven refinery has a rated capacity of 108,000
barrels per day. Amoco sells about 2 percent of the gasoline sold in
the United Kingdom.
</TEXT>
